<h1> Hypothesis Statement </h1>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
    <h2>Overview:</h2>
     <p>Our customers, their problems, our propsed solutions are all based in some amount of uncertainity. We put our own congnitive bias in everything we do and we need to ensure
      that we are aware of the assumptons we are making and can prove our disprove our assumptions. To do this, we will turn our assumptions into hypotheses to be validated. <br /><br />
        Remember, hpotheses can be in looked at in 3 different aspects.
        <ul>
        <li><b>Desirable</b> - wanted or wished for as being an attractive, useful, or necessary course of action. <br />Do our customers want us to build it</li>
        <li><b>Feasible </b>- possible to do easily or conveniently<br />Can we build it</li>
        <li><b>Viable </b> - capable of working successfully<br />Should we build it</li>

      </div>
  </div>

